defs.docs: A pure-Rust library to work with Linux capabilities.

attributes.value: ! A pure-Rust library to work with Linux capabilities.
! It provides support for manipulating capabilities available
! in modern Linux kernel. It supports traditional POSIX sets
! (Effective, Inheritable, Permitted) as well as Linux-specific
! This module exposes methods to perform detection of kernel
! features at runtime. This allows applications to auto-detect

defs.name: ambient_set_supported
defs.docs: Check whether the running kernel supports the ambient set.

attributes.value: / Check whether the running kernel supports the ambient set.
/ Ambient set was introduced in Linux kernel 4.3. On recent kernels
/ where the ambient set is supported, this will return `Ok`.
/ On a legacy kernel, an `Err` is returned instead.

defs.docs: Check if a thread contains a capability in a set.

attributes.value: / Check if a thread contains a capability in a set.
/ Check if set `cset` for thread `tid` contains capability `cap`.
/ If `tid` is `None`, this operates on current thread (tid=0).
/ It cannot check Ambient or Bounding capabilities of other processes.

defs.name: read
defs.docs: Return all capabilities in a set for a thread.

attributes.value: / Return all capabilities in a set for a thread.
/ Return current content of set `cset` for thread `tid`.
/ If `tid` is `None`, this operates on current thread (tid=0).
/ It cannot read Ambient or Bounding capabilities of other processes.

defs.name: set
defs.value: fn (tid: Option<i32>, cset: CapSet, value: CapsHashSet) -> Result<()>
defs.docs: Set a capability set for a thread to a new value.

attributes.value: / Set a capability set for a thread to a new value.
/ All and only capabilities in `value` will be set for set `cset` for thread `tid`.
/ If `tid` is `None`, this operates on current thread (tid=0).
/ It cannot manipulate Ambient set of other processes.
/ Capabilities cannot be set in Bounding set.

defs.name: clear
defs.docs: Clear all capabilities in a set for a thread.

attributes.value: / Clear all capabilities in a set for a thread.
/ All capabilities will be cleared from set `cset` for thread `tid`.
/ If `tid` is `None`, this operates on current thread (tid=0).
/ It cannot manipulate Ambient or Bounding set of other processes.

defs.name: raise
defs.value: fn (tid: Option<i32>, cset: CapSet, cap: Capability) -> Result<()>
defs.docs: Raise a single capability in a set for a thread.

attributes.value: / Raise a single capability in a set for a thread.
/ Capabilities `cap` will be raised from set `cset` of thread `tid`.
/ If `tid` is `None`, this operates on current thread (tid=0).
/ It cannot manipulate Ambient set of other processes.
/ Capabilities cannot be raised in Bounding set.

defs.docs: Drop a single capability from a set for a thread.

attributes.value: / Drop a single capability from a set for a thread.
